This paper is primarily concerned with the use of persistence diagrams in machine learning, specifically in the context of embedding them into Reproducing Kernel Hilbert Spaces (RKHS). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the theoretical foundations and practical applications of machine learning algorithms. 

The paper also involves some computational geometry, as it discusses the metric properties of the embedding, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as a possible sub-category. 

Since the paper involves the analysis of distances and stability guarantees, it could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), respectively. 

Finally, the paper's focus on topological data analysis and its use of persistence diagrams suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which deals with the analysis of complex networks and data structures.
